Byte-preservation guard (for Plan 02's import rewrite)
------------------------------------------------------
When Plan 02 ports the borrowed files and rewrites their import paths to this repo's
remapping aliases, the licence-header and SPDX lines MUST remain byte-identical to the
upstream source. Any in-place rewrite (e.g. sed) MUST anchor ONLY on `^import .*from "`
lines (the curly-brace import form Panoptic V2 uses) and MUST NEVER touch `//` comment
or `// SPDX-License-Identifier:` lines. This keeps each borrowed file's provenance and
licence attribution intact and byte-identical to the frozen audit snapshot.

Single-compile note (intentional, not a gap)
---------------------------------------------
FORK-01's roadmap wording references a multi-version solc matrix; 07-RESEARCH §5
retired it — Panoptic V2 is `^0.8.24` for every file, so this repo uses a single
`evm_version="cancun"` / `solc 0.8.24` compile profile. This is intentional, not a gap.
